  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI cannot get ethers typescript tests to work.\r\n\r\nTest file:\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\n/// <reference types=\"@nomiclabs/buidler-ethers/src/type-extensions\" />\r\nimport { expect } from 'chai';\r\n\r\ndescribe('Greeter', function () {\r\n\tit(\"Should return the new greeting once it's changed\", async function () {\r\n\t\tconst Greeter = await ethers.getContractFactory('Greeter');\r\n\t\tconst greeter = await Greeter.deploy('Hello, world!');\r\n\r\n\t\tawait greeter.deployed();\r\n\t\texpect(await greeter.greet()).to.equal('Hello, world!');\r\n\r\n\t\tawait greeter.setGreeting('Hola, mundo!');\r\n\t\texpect(await greeter.greet()).to.equal('Hola, mundo!');\r\n\t});\r\n});\r\n```\r\nError:\r\n```\r\nAn unexpected error occurred:\r\n\r\nTSError: тип Unable to compile TypeScript:\r\ntest/Greeter.test.ts:6:25 - error TS2304: Cannot find name 'ethers'.\r\n\r\n6  \tconst Greeter = await ethers.getContractFactory('Greeter');\t                      ~~~~~~\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow do I get it to recognise the ethers global?",
